            "content": "## Summary\n\nAudit of the monorepo's organization and build configuration against the official Turborepo examples (`with-nestjs`, `kitchen-sink` — the latter is the canonical Package-Configuration pattern for a Next+Node-API workspace), current Turborepo 2.x / Next.js 16 / NestJS 11 docs and release notes, and comparable OSS monorepos (cal.com, documenso, dub, midday). Everything actionable is applied here; everything evaluated-and-rejected is listed at the bottom with reasons.\n\n### Bugs found by the audit\n\n- **`apps/api` `start:prod` was broken as shipped.** Root-level `drizzle.config.ts` was part of the build input set, which pulled TypeScript's inferred `rootDir` up to the package root — the entrypoint compiled to `dist/src/main.js` while `start:prod` runs `node dist/main`. It's now excluded from `tsconfig.build.json` (drizzle-kit loads the `.ts` directly and never needs the compiled copy). Verified: `dist/` is flat, `node dist/main` boots and serves `/docs/json`, SIGTERM terminates cleanly.\n- **Nest shutdown hooks were never enabled.** They're off by default; without `app.enableShutdownHooks()` SIGTERM never reaches `onModuleDestroy`/`onApplicationShutdown`, so the postgres.js pool and pg-boss client can't drain — required by the clean-shutdown invariants in `docs/scaling.md` and increasingly load-bearing once the worker split (#50) runs replicas behind an orchestrator.\n\n### Build caching, made real\n\n- The root `build` task declared only `.next/**` outputs, so **`api#build` was silently uncacheable** (turbo's \"no output files found\" warning — a cache hit restored nothing). Following the kitchen-sink Package Configuration pattern: `apps/api/turbo.json` declares `dist/**` + `openapi.json`; `apps/web/turbo.json` owns `.next/**` (minus `.next/cache`) plus its build env (`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`, `NEXT_RUNTIME`; `SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN` as `passThroughEnv` so the secret doesn't enter cache hashes).\n- `globalEnv` trimmed to the truly global (`CI`, `NODE_ENV`) — per-task `env` everywhere else, per Turborepo's own guidance (cal.com's ~250-entry `globalEnv` is the community cautionary tale). `.node-version` added to `globalDependencies`.\n- `test` is now a first-class cached turbo task; `apps/api`'s override hashes the suite-gating vars (`POSTGRES_URL`, `TEST_DATABASE_URL`, `RUN_MODEL_EVALS`) so a cached \"skipped\" run can't mask a gated one. CI runs `turbo run test` instead of a raw `pnpm --filter`.\n- CI persists the turbo local cache with `actions/cache` (exact-key per commit, prefix fallback). Workflow passes `actionlint` and `zizmor`.\n\n**Measured:** warm `turbo build` = `FULL TURBO`, ~1.8s for both apps (api was a guaranteed rebuild before).\n\n### Web\n\n- `typedRoutes: true` (stable since 15.5). Three touchpoints needed types, all legitimate: the login open-redirect sanitizer now *returns* `Route` (the cast is the guard's contract), `loginRedirectPath`, and the sidebar `NavItem.href`.\n- Audit validated the existing config as already-correct: `turbopack.root` (worktree-safe), `transpilePackages`, `proxy.ts`, Sentry Turbopack setup. No `<Image quality>` usage, so Next 16's `images.qualities` default change is a non-issue.\n\n### Hygiene\n\n- `$schema` → `turborepo.dev` (old URL 301s), root package `shadcn-ui-monorepo` → `llame`, contradictory pnpm `ignoredBuiltDependencies`/`onlyBuiltDependencies` overlap resolved, root `test`/`typecheck` convenience scripts.\n\n### Evaluated and deliberately not adopted\n\n| Item | Why not |\n| --- | --- |\n| `turbopackFileSystemCacheForBuild` (2.3–5.5× warm builds) | Experimental; interaction with Sentry's debug-ID injection pass is unverified — worth a smoke test on a branch after the 16.3 upgrade |\n| Vercel Remote Cache / self-hosted cache server | `actions/cache` gets same-repo incremental caching with zero external accounts; remote cache is the next step if CI time hurts across runners |\n| Nest SWC builder | The tsc-emit + tsgo-typecheck split already covers both speed and full-program correctness; SWC has open rough edges (plugin incompat, nest-cli#3139) |\n| `turbo boundaries` / tags | Experimental, RFC-stage |\n| `check-types` / `packages/tsconfig` renames | Cosmetic ecosystem alignment; churn without benefit — no canonical convention exists across sampled repos |\n| pnpm `catalog:` | Worth adopting when more packages share pinned deps; premature at two packages |\n| `--affected` CI gating | The biggest lever per the field survey (midday's pattern) — deferred until CI time actually hurts |\n\n## Verification\n\n- Cold `turbo build` green; warm build `FULL TURBO` ~1.8s; `openapi.json` byte-identical after the dist-path change (CI's contract guard stays green).\n- `node dist/main` boots against local Postgres, serves `/docs/json`, exits cleanly on SIGTERM.\n- `turbo run test` (api 120 passed, web 18 passed), `turbo run lint`, `turbo run typecheck` all green; prettier clean; `actionlint` + `zizmor` clean on the workflow.\n",
